Let me reintroduce myself My names Emily, Im an Exercise Physiologist and thats a big part of whats behind the uplifting, positive energy you see on this page. I actually started on Musical.ly back in the day, just being an uplifting, positive influencer and I genuinely think that energy helped guide me into a career in EP. At my core, Im driven by values like kindness, growth, authenticity, resilience, and connection and I truly believe that movement, both physical and emotional, has the power to support all of those things. Even the smallest actions can make life feel more meaningful. For a while, I was nervous to share more of this side of my life like my work, my knowledge, my passion because I didnt feel qualified enough. But Ive come to realise that your story the ups, the uncertainties, and the growth is what truly matters. So heres to sharing more of my journey and hopefully inspiring you to lean into what feels good for your mind, body, and whole self  #ExercisePhysiology #TikTokIntro #KindnessAndMovement #MentalHealthMatters #GrowthJourney #FeelGoodFitness #MovementIsMedicine #LiveWithHeart #fyp

At this point in my life, I was so obsessed with how I thought my body needed to look. I constantly compared myself to girls I saw on TikTok and Instagram, wondering why my dieting and training didnt make me look like them. Ive always struggled with my mental health  and still do  but back then, I tied my worth to how I looked. Since taking this video, Ive gained weight, and for a long time, I felt ashamed of that. But Ive also grown in so many ways. Ive learned to care for my body, not punish it. To move, eat, and rest with love, not guilt. And most importantly, Ive started to put my mental health first. Its heartbreaking how much pressure women feel to look a certain way. But our bodies do so much for us  and they deserve respect at every stage. Im still on this journey of self-love, but Im in a much healthier, more positive place now. Im surrounded by people who love me for who I am  not what I look like. Family, friends, and a partner who remind me daily that Im enough. Im so grateful for how far Ive come, and even more grateful for the growth still to come. If youre struggling, youre not alone. Be kind to your body, and even kinder to your mind.  #SelfLoveJourney #MentalHealthAwareness #BodyAcceptance #ProgressNotPerfection #GratefulHeart

When I first moved from Japan to New York City, I was terrified. I didnt know anyone, didnt fully know the language, and had no idea what the future would look like. All I had was a suitcase, a dream, and a heart full of uncertainty. I cried in secret, doubted myself often, and questioned whether I belonged. But somehow, step by shaky step, I built a life  a home  in this city that once felt so intimidating. Now, Im moving again. But this time, its different. Im not alone. I have my family with me, and instead of fear, I feel excitement. Instead of wondering if Ill survive, I know Ill thrive. Because Ive done it before  and Ive grown into a woman who knows her strength. To any woman out there standing on the edge of the unknown: its okay to be scared. But dont let that fear stop you. You are capable of creating magic in places that feel unfamiliar. Trust yourself. Youve got this #lifeupdate #storytime #movingtoaustin #newmomlife #newparent

what you're not changing, you're choosing  Sometimes, we don't feel empowered enough or confident enough to step into our next season. Sometimes we already feel so overwhelmed by the day-to-day that we don't even consider how we could move forward. But if you could take 10 minutes today to sit down and ask yourself, what things you are choosing, that consistently hold you back, it could be a life changer. You might also recognize some hard things that you ARE choosing, because you see how they DO benefit you (or how they might in the future) and that alone can be so empowering. It could be a reminder that although things are tough right now, you know where you are headed and that's worth it. You have so much more control than you think you have. Don't ask yourself what other people want from you. Don't ask yourself what's going to make you look good. Ask yourself what hard things in your life YOU want to choose because this is YOUR life!  #advice #adviceforwomen #selfgrowth #selfgrowthjourney #mindset #mindsetmatters
